Governor Okezie Ikpeazu of Abia State has felicitated with Chief Tony Ukasanya on his birthday. Ukasanya is the pioneer Chairman of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, in the State. The governor described the chieftain as an astute political tactician and experienced party administrator whose wealth of experience in party politics has remained a powerful resource material for successive leaders in Abia State. Governor Ikpeazu in a congratulatory message made available to newsmen by his Chief Press Secretary, Onyebuchi Ememanka, on Thursday night, noted with firm view that the political deftness and depth of Chief Tony Ukasanya’s experience has remained a powerful tool for the stabilization of the political environment in the State. According to the message, “the Governor is grateful to God for his kindness to Chief Ukasanya and for keeping him to be a living source of inspiration to today’s generation of political leaders”. Governor Ikpeazu, on behalf of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) family in the state, the Government and People of Abia State wished Chief Tony Ukasanya ”a very happy birthday and prayed the Almighty God to grant him many more years of service to our people.”